transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Hello.

Speaker 2: Hello, Mr. Antonio De Luca? In New York?

Speaker 1: Yeah. Yeah. I want to check my prescription.

Speaker 2: Okay, I'll just pull your prescription.

Speaker 1: You have a prescription, 10 tablets from Dr. Mayer for Viagra AGV 100 mg.

Speaker 2: You just don't need your refill at the moment?

Speaker 1: I can advise the pharmacy to pause and you can just order as needed later.

Speaker 2: Can you repeat what you said again?

Speaker 1: I can have the pharmacy pausing your prescription if you don't need it at the moment,

Speaker 2: so you can just order as needed.

Speaker 1: No, I just want to cancel it.

Speaker 2: Okay. Just be advised that the company financed a doctor prescription,

Speaker 1: so that being said, if you try to reorder in the future,

Speaker 2: they're going to have to get you a new one, and that will impact your price.

Speaker 1: I just want you to be aware of that.

Speaker 2: That's why they offer to pause when you don't need your prescription,

Speaker 1: so that way you can get it once or twice a year maybe,

Speaker 2: but you don't have to get it every 30 days or every other month,

Speaker 1: so you don't get refill often, but you still have access to your Viagra anytime

Speaker 2: and at a good price too.

Speaker 1: Yeah, let's pause it.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: They're going to pause you up to half a year,

Speaker 2: so you don't get it on a monthly basis anymore.

Speaker 1: You can call to reorder. You can log in your account, okay?

Speaker 2: I'm advising the pharmacy that you're not active right now to put a pause,

Speaker 1: preserve the prescription, and lock your price in, okay?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I just need it maybe once or twice a year, and that's it.

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's fine.

Speaker 2: Whatever you need, you just let us know,

Speaker 1: and we're making adjustments at your liking because it's your prescription,

Speaker 2: so you can do whatever you want to do with it, get it often, get it less often.

Speaker 1: You just communicate, you know?

Speaker 2: All right. Okay.

Speaker 1: Everything is paused for now, and give us a call to reorder as well, okay?

Speaker 2: Okay. Thank you.

Speaker 1: All right, Mr. DeLuca. You have a good one, okay?

Speaker 2: Thank you. Bye.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
